-- Polish Stocks: Dom Maklerski IDM, PKO Bank Polski Are Active
-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 2012-07-04T12:15:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/polish-stocks-dom-maklerski-idm-pko-bank-polski-are-active.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  eased 0.1
percent to 2,268.05 as of 1:43 p.m. in Warsaw.  The following are among the most active equities on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Dom Maklerski IDM SA (IDM PW), a Polish brokerage, slumped
15 percent to 1.04 zloty, a three-year low. Sky Club, the Polish
tour operator that filed for bankruptcy today, received as much
as 12 million zloty ($3.6 million) of financing from IDM SA,
Agnieszka Dral, a Sky Club board member, said at a news
conference in Warsaw.  PKO Bank Polski SA (PKO)   fell 0.9 percent to 33.4 zloty.
Poland’s state-owned bank fell for a third day since Treasury
Minister Mikolaj Budzanowski said on July 2 the government will
sell its stake through 2013.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
